column5: TOTALLY BLOWN OUT. Passed over the river in Angus and Ivy this morning,and you couldnt even see the mouth of Bear Creek.
Ya, it came up about 3 feet overnight and already dropped back a few inches, a little puddle in the Angus plaza from the Pine going over the banks too.
Yep seen that this morning,going into the giant tiger. Trout are going to be up and back before opening.
